  "text": "Food webs are also now at the point where we understand what attributes reliably reflect degradation and vulnerability to future change. For example, marine food webs that have been degraded have simpler food web structure (shorter food chains, less trophic loops, and lower connectivity), with likely consequences for food web stability [CITATION_1] . Food webs have not yet been used as indices of degradation, in a systematic sense. However, particularly in marine environments, we are well positioned to apply food webs in this way [CITATION_2] .",
